RS RED FLAG 1 — EXCEL INPUT FLEXIBILITY:
The RS workflow currently supports only unit-composition Excel with strength columns. Extend to support all valid RS Excel types without regressing the existing flow.

Add classifier that auto-detects mode:
- detailed_rs_calculation
- unit_composition_strength_columns (current)
- combined_workbook (both sheets present)
- component_mdd_only
- insufficient

Type A (existing, preserve): unit composition Excel
  Ingredient | Compendia Status | 40 mg | 20 mg | 10 mg | Stage
  User provides MDD; system derives no_of_doses and amount_in_maximum_dose.

Type B (add): detailed RS calculation Excel
  Contains: No. of doses, Components, Quantity / unit (mg), Amount in Maximum Dose (mg),
  per-solvent Limit (ppm) + Daily Exposure (mg) for Ethanol, Ethylene Glycol, 1,4-Dioxane,
  Iso Propyl Alcohol, Tertiary butyl alcohol, Heptane, Acetone, Methanol, Toluene,
  Drug Product row, Total Daily Exposure row (with equivalent ppm + exposure mg),
  Residual solvent Limit as per current USP <467> row.
  Behavior: Excel is the primary calculation source. Use Excel values directly for Section 5
  tables, Drug Product totals, Total Daily Exposure equivalent ppm, USP <467> comparison.
  Annexures become traceability evidence only. Missing annexure = warning, not blocker.
  Do not recalculate from annexures. Do not invent missing values. Do not hallucinate.
  Do not derive 20 mg / 10 mg from 40 mg. Do not over-interpret generic supplier policy
  statements as material-specific limits. q.s. process solvent rows with numeric quantity
  in the calculation sheet must be respected (do not silently skip).

Type C (add): combined workbook
  Sheet 1 matches unit-composition pattern (Type A style).
  Sheet 2 matches detailed RS calculation pattern (Type B style).
  Optional Sheet 3: cumulative composition by stage.
  Behavior: Unit composition sheet drives Section 4 Table 2. Detailed RS calculation sheet
  drives Section 5 tables. Annexures evidence-only.

Type D (component_mdd_only): use component-level MDD directly (no strength derivation).
Insufficient: warn, ask for richer input. Do not silently zero.

Universal calculation rules (preserve):
- Daily Exposure (mg/day) = Amount in Maximum Dose (mg/day) × Limit (ppm) / 1,000,000.
- Total equivalent ppm in Total Daily Exposure row = total_exposure_mg × 1,000,000 / Drug_Product_amount_in_maximum_dose_mg.
- Confirmed no-contribution cells render 0/0. Unresolved cells render blank/NR + warning.
- Aggregate equivalent materials before calculation (Hydroxypropyl Cellulose ↔ Hydroxy Propyl Cellulose ↔ HPC ↔ Klucel EF; Talc; Triethyl citrate; Polysorbate 80; Yellow Iron Oxide).

