CONVERTER PROMPT RULES:
- No solvent_name-style field; only deg_eg_evidence applies.
- Phrases like Class 1/2/3 solvents, OVI, ICH Q3C solvents, USP <467> solvents, other residual solvents, residual solvents, water are evidence scopes, not DEG/EG limits.
- "Class 1/2/3 residual solvents excluded by manufacturing process" → declaration_scopes with evidence_type=excluded_by_process; no DEG/EG numeric inference.
- Generic supplier policy/regulatory discussion (e.g. Merck letter discussing EG PDE updates) must not assign material-specific numeric DEG/EG limits. Use evidence_type=policy_statement; deg_present/eg_present=Unknown unless the named material is explicitly linked to a numeric value.
- Vendor CoA with explicit numeric EG/DEG (e.g. NMT 620 ppm via USP <469>) is the only valid source for deg_eg_evidence numeric values.
- USP/NF monographs alone are insufficient unless monograph explicitly states a DEG or EG numeric limit.
- If body has no material identity, infer material_name from filename, set material_name_source=filename_inferred, needs_material_confirmation=true. Never use document_title as material_name.
- Generic document titles (Residual Solvents, Residual Solvent Declaration, Quality Statement, Regulatory Information, Certificate of Analysis, Specification) must never become material_name.

ANNEXURE MAPPING (REUSE EI INJECTION RESOLVER):
- Reuse the EI injection identity resolver architecture exactly because it is the working baseline.
- Adapt RS/DEG-EG vocabulary (same vocabulary list as Part A above).
- Negative-pair protection: TEC ≠ ATBC. Generic tokens alone must not drive matches.
- Reject generic material names unless real identity found elsewhere.
- Auto-map all components.
- Mapping confidence is audit info only.
- Do not require user confirmation.
- No mapping issue blocks generation.

ASSESSMENT BUILDING:
- For each composition material (excluding water/q.s. unless explicitly required), build assessment_table row: material_code, ingredient, deg_present, eg_present, specification_limit.
- Defaults: Unknown (not No), Specification limit = Not applicable.
- If matched annexure provides explicit numeric evidence → use it.
- If matched annexure has only policy/regulatory discussion → Unknown.
- If matched annexure has excluded_by_process or no_source negative declaration → No for both, Specification limit = Not applicable.
- For any material where deg_present=Yes or eg_present=Yes → create one detail_tables entry with material, intro, caption, columns (USP Monograph, Vendor COA, DRL Specification, DRL Specification No.), rows, inference text.
- Multi-positive case: multiple detail_tables entries.

